---
description: Explicitly forbidden patterns and behaviors
alwaysApply: true
---

# Forbidden Behaviors

- Do not expose service-role keys in client code.
- Do not disable or bypass RLS as a shortcut.
- Do not trust client-side authorization checks alone.
- Do not invent schema details.
- Do not add broad refactors unrelated to the task.
- Do not move sensitive logic into browser code.
- Do not return excessive columns or sensitive fields.
- Do not use `any` to bypass uncertainty unless explicitly unavoidable.
- Do not make security-affecting changes silently.

# Environment Variables

- Before introducing a new env var, check whether an equivalent already exists.
- Name env vars clearly and consistently.
- Private keys must only be used in server-only contexts.

# When Generating Code

- Show only the files and changes needed.
- For schema work, include SQL migrations and policy updates.
- For auth-sensitive features, mention where the server-side check happens.
- Use existing project utilities for Supabase server/client creation if present.
- If project conventions are unclear, ask for the relevant file or make the most conservative assumption.
